verbose_text: Since our working hypothesis is that G-1 genes include genes that regulate the expression of G-2 genes, we examined the interactions between 69 G-1 and 96 G-2 genes using IPA, and found 5 direct and 3 indirect interactions (XREF_TABLE and XREF_FIG) : Rxrg and group specific component (Gc) interacted with cytochrome P450 subfamily 24 (Cyp24a1); Bcl6 interacted with the following 3 genes : Zbtb16, protocadherin 9 (Pcdh9) and Spi-B transcription factor (Spib); Cftr interacted with Ephx2; tumor protein p73 (Tp73) interacted with tetraspanin 1 (Tspan1); and Sox2 interacted with Tp73.
